To run the analysis:
===================

0) Modifications:
------------------

Modify the following files, if needed:

* HPlusHadronic_x.txt	rates & uncertainties for mH=x
* input_ett		efficiency of tt
* input_luminosity	luminosity
* input_nrest		sum of dibosons, single top and Drell-Yan
* input_nttww		N tt->WW
* input_nwjets		N W+jets
* input_sigma		sigma_tt of SM


1) obtain LandS software from http://mschen.web.cern.ch/mschen/lands/:
------------------------------------------------------------------------

wget http://mschen-exp.web.cern.ch/mschen-exp/Statistics/lands.tgz
tar -xzf lands.tgz
cmsenv
# compile LandS
# NOTE: if LandS version has changed, update the name of the directory 
cd LandS_20101116; 
gmake clean; gmake all;
cd ..


2) modify the LandS datacard and run LandS
-------------------------------------------------------------

./script_run_LandS


3) run the ROOT analysis to obtain Br limit (mH,Br)
---------------------------------------------------

root -l -b -q brlimit.C

*As a result, the br limit plot brlimits.png/eps is generated


4) run the python analysis to obtain MSSM limit (mH,tanB)
---------------------------------------------------------

./mssmLimit.py

*As a result, the tanB limit plot mssmLimit.png is generated
